{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17533750","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17533750"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T16:39:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T16:39:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14868"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14868","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14868"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.12,0.02,0.75,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7559"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102417"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7559","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7559"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14868"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84891"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"15"},{"type":"tags","id":"39"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"486"},{"type":"tags","id":"974"},{"type":"tags","id":"1196"},{"type":"tags","id":"1659"},{"type":"tags","id":"2232"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4969"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18487"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35603"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40324"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102417","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/102417"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old woman is reviewed in the transplant clinic three weeks after receiving a cadaveric renal transplant. She has no significant medical history apart from end-stage kidney disease secondary to IgA nephropathy. Her current medications include tacrolimus, mycophenolate, prednisolone, and valganciclovir. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Her surgical wound is healing well.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate prophylaxis against Pneumocystis jirovecii pneumonia?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Dapsone","Azithromycin","Pentamidine nebuliser","Trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole","Fluconazole"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient requires prophylaxis against \u003Cem\u003EPneumocystis jirovecii\u003C/em\u003E pneumonia (PJP) following solid organ transplantation. \u003Cstrong\u003ETrimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole\u003C/strong\u003E is the first-line agent for PJP prophylaxis due to its excellent efficacy, good safety profile, and additional protection against other opportunistic pathogens such as \u003Cem\u003EToxoplasma gondii\u003C/em\u003E and \u003Cem\u003ENocardia\u003C/em\u003E species.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDapsone\u003C/strong\u003E is an alternative prophylactic agent for PJP in patients who cannot receive trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole (e.g., due to sulfa allergy or intolerance). While effective, it does not provide the broader antimicrobial coverage of trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPentamidine\u003C/strong\u003E nebuliser is another alternative for PJP prophylaxis but is generally considered as an alternative due to the need for monthly administration in a healthcare setting and potential for bronchospasm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAzithromycin\u003C/strong\u003E is not indicated for PJP prophylaxis. While it may be used for prophylaxis against non-tuberculous mycobacterial infections in some immunocompromised patients, it is not effective against \u003Cem\u003EP. jirovecii\u003C/em\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFluconazole\u003C/strong\u003E is a systemic antifungal used for prophylaxis against candida infections in immunosuppressed patients but has no role in PJP prevention.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pneumocystis jirovecii pneumonia prophylaxis is important for solid organ and hematopoietic stem cell transplant recipients.","Trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole is the preferred PJP prophylaxis due to its efficacy and additional protection against other opportunistic pathogens."],"references":["Antibiotic. In: Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited; accessed {04 Nov 2024}. https://www.tg.org.au","Weyant RB, Kabbani D, Doucette K, Lau C, Cervera C. Pneumocystis jirovecii: a review with a focus on prevention and treatment. Expert Opin Pharmacother. 2021 Aug;22(12):1579-1592. doi: 10.1080/14656566.2021.1915989. Epub 2021 Apr 19. PMID: 33870843. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33870843/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84891"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14868"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84891","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/84891"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-12T16:58:18+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-12T16:59:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7559"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102417"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"15",